# Testing (Affirmations)

## Setup

- **`renderWithContext`** when the tree needs global providers.
- **`renderRouterWithContext`** for Expo Router / modal routes (pass route map object).

## Queries

- **First discovery of UI:** prefer **`await screen.findBy*`** (role, text, testId) so the test waits.
- After something is known on screen, **`getBy*`** is fine.
- **Avoid** `waitFor` **only** to poll until `getBy*` succeeds — use **`findBy*`** instead.
- Scope with **`within(element)`** when asserting inside a card/row.

## Behavior

- Test **what users see and do** (press, type, see message) — not internal React state.
- **Async:** after `fireEvent.press`, use **`findBy*`** (or `await findByText`) for outcomes.
- **`act`** when needed for navigation/async bursts (see **`.cursorrules`** examples).

## Mocks

- Mock **external** modules (storage, notifications, time) — not all of `react`.
- **`jest.requireActual`** when partially overriding a module.
- Reset **`mockClear`** / relevant mocks in **`beforeEach`**.

## Shared utilities

Use **`@testing/renderWithContext`**, **`@testing/dateTimePickerMock`** (and similar) when they already exist for the pattern you need.

Extended examples, pitfalls, and summaries: **`.cursorrules`** (Testing sections).
